choices.text:
searching for social events. Mostly I found opportunities for free time. Work is OK and I must say I earned quite a bit of money there, but finding opportunities is pretty hard. 

I am a Dance Master from Uruguay. I won a scholarship for social dance research. With a team of lovely ladies plus my fantastic fiancee, we (meaning she) are making a neat little 14 class series for free awareness sessions.  So far we have reached about 3500 people!
We ask for people to donate to a shelter for young people. The shelters will not always take in single women or men. The kids are more difficult to raise. Many programs are difficult to negotiate. They get government funding, but for anything they have to have funding. We raised around $100 dollars the first night and some of them turn around and ask for extra! 

This next session will be boxing for durability, as our health ministry suggests. If people want to continue to participate in Physical Activities, we are also offering capoeira. Also for free!

I offering dance masters, so I also want to spread my love for dance. I have created classes in different cities in am going to have some lectures in different places around the country. This week I had my first one in Stockton.

This is all about mentoring. I plan on talking about my experiences and share a bit of my story. I want to ask; What is your biggest new for the future?

Where do see yourself in 10
